# Guide blocks: editorial note vs callout

When the user says **"editorial note"**, use `EditorialNote` from `@/components/EditorialNote`.

When the user says **"callout"**, use `GuideCallout` from `@/components/GuideCallout`.

When the user says **"support callout"**, use `SupportCallout` via `PageFoot` from `@/components/PageFoot` (before Further reading and Sources on every page).

Full spec: `src/lib/guide-blocks.ts` (`EDITORIAL_NOTE_BLOCK`, `CALLOUT_BLOCK`, `SUPPORT_CALLOUT_BLOCK`).

## Editorial note

- **Job:** Who the page is for, editorial framing, cautions.
- **Look:** Muted grey fill. Left bar muted grey. Tiny uppercase muted label. Tight sans body.
- **Example:** Home page — "Who this is for".
- **DOM:** `data-guide-block="editorial-note"`

## Callout

- **Job:** Practical tips, tests, scope, in-page orientation ("how to tell…").
- **Look:** Primary-tint fill. Left bar primary red. Title in tiny uppercase primary sans; body in serif (or tight sans if `compact`).
- **Examples:** Home — "Not sure which phase you are in?"; Procurement — Scope.
- **DOM:** `data-guide-block="callout"`

## Support callout

- **Job:** Standing help pointer at the foot of every page (before Further reading and Sources).
- **Look:** Reuses Doorway card anatomy — small-caps label "SUPPORT AND COMMUNITIES", prose line, arrow link "Browse the support communities →".
- **Variants:** Generic, or page-specific contact linked inline on thread pages (Security, Procurement, Privacy, Accessibility, User research, Dependencies and standards, Data stewardship).
- **DOM:** `data-guide-block="support-callout"`

## Do not

- Use EditorialNote for practical how-to / phase tests.
- Use GuideCallout for audience framing ("who this is for").
- Treat DoorwayBlock, CautionBlock, or LookingAhead as interchangeable with these two.

## Card fill (clickable vs static)

- **Clickable cards** (whole card navigates or opens a dialog): cream fill via `guideClickableCardFillStyle` from `@/lib/guide-cards`.
- **Static cards** (decorative / informational only): outline only — `guideStaticCardClassName` (`bg-transparent`), no cream fill.
- Canonical constants and class names live in `src/lib/guide-cards.ts`; `PracticeCard` re-exports them for interactive card shells.

## List vs prose enumerations

- **Thread-page intros (lead paragraphs):** always flowing prose — never a bullet list, even for four or more items.
- **Short inline enumerations elsewhere (three or fewer items):** keep as inline prose in the sentence.
- **Four or more items in body content** (not the lead): render as a real list (`guideListMinCount` in `@/lib/thread-rich-content`).
- **Whose job it is:** intro line is prose; roles use `InlineArrowLeadList` (bold lead + body on one line, rust arrow) — same as Sunset “replace or retire” fork bullets.
- **Body list indent:** all body bullet and numbered lists use `guideListIndent` (`pl-6 md:pl-8`), including `InlineArrowLeadList`, `guideArrowList`, and `ArrowLeadList`. Navigation, card grids, and footer link lists stay flush.
